node.text: Watch Remo Ruffini for @moncler accept the Business Leader award presented to him by @shailenewoodley. This award recognises the work of an industry leader of a fashion and/or luxury business who has overseen both creative and commercial success in the past year. This does not have to be a CEO or president but someone who has shown leadership in digital transformation, innovation, creativity and commercial growth. Visit the link in bio to see all the highlights from the #FashionAwards.

Watch Rejina Pyo for @rejinapyo receive the British Emerging Talent - Womenswear award from @belpowley and @gugumbatharaw at The #FashionAwards 2019! The award celebrates a British womenswear Designer/Creative Director or business that has been instrumental in innovating and leading women’s fashion over the last year – excelling both creatively and commercially, creating an impressive footprint on the global fashion stage. To see more highlights from the event visit link in bio.

Watch Daniel Lee for @bottegaveneta win the British Designer of the Year - Womenswear award, presented by @emmaroberts. The award celebrates a British womenswear Designer/Creative Director or business that has been instrumental in innovating and leading women’s fashion over the last year – excelling both creatively and commercially, creating an impressive footprint on the global fashion stage. To see more highlights from the event visit link in bio. #FashionAwards

Watch Daniel Lee for @bottegaveneta receive the Accessories Designer of the Year Award at The #FashionAwards 2019 presented by @misskarenelson. The award celebrates a Designer that has proved instrumental in elevating accessories to the forefront of the fashion industry, demonstrating a skill for both creativity and commerce, and establishing their brand as a global fashion leader. To see more highlights from the event visit link in bio.

British Fashion Council’s CEO, Caroline Rush and Chair, Stephanie Phair were joined on Friday evening by members of the #BFC Advisory Board, Patrons, Pillar Presidents, Press Committee, #PositiveFashion Committee and Designer Members to celebrate the beginning of the Christmas break with festive drinks at the Treehouse Hotel London in Marylebone.

@realbarbarapalvin wearing her @togetherbandofficial friendship band at the #FashionAwards 2019. #TOGETHERBAND is a non-profit campaign which champions the UN Sustainable Development Goals for a sustainable future. The campaign is a partnership between British sustainable accessories brand @bottletoppers, the @UNFoundation and @UBS who create bands made from upcycled ocean plastic and repurposed illegal fire-arm metal. Each friendship band represents a different UN Sustainable Development Goal. #CHOOSEYOURGOAL

Calling all designers! Applications for the 2020 BFC/Vogue Designer Fashion Fund are now open. The Fund aims to discover new talent and accelerate growth over a 12 month mentoring period and a cash prize of £200,000! Previous recipients include @walesbonner, @mollygoddard, @motherofpearl and @palmerharding. To apply visit link in bio.

“In order to understand which trends to move on, brands should be speaking to everyone in the company to get a view of their true customer. This includes the interns, everyone has a voice! Companies also need to focus on hiring a diverse group of people to reflect who your customer is”
